This paper deals with the concept of entropy and its variance, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of binary data elements and their transformation, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the correlation between the transformed data elements, which is a topic of interest in signal processing (cs.SI) and information systems (cs.IS).
